    "Once two stations are connected in the same cluster at a lower level, these two stations will never be categorized into different clusters at a higher level.",
    "The second approach is the partitioning-optimization approach, in which the number of clusters is first determined, followed by clustering using a measure of similarity between observations.",
    "The clustering results depend on the initial clusters, which must be determined beforehand.",
    "The robustness of these initial clusters can be examined by conducting clustering with different sets of initial clusters.",
    "However, achieving a global minimum solution is not guaranteed."
